[1] Norovirus, suspected, courthouse - Canada (Vancouver, BC)
Date: Thu 22 Apr 2004
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: Yahoo News, Canada, Wed 21 Apr 2004 [edited]
<http://story.news.yahoo.com/news?tmpl=story&cid=2155&ncid=2155&e=1&u=/cpress/20040422/ca_pr_on_he/court_norwalk_infection>


Canada: norovirus outbreak affects Vancouver courthouse
-----------------------------------------------
More than legal judgements are being handed out at Vancouver's
provincial court. [A norovirus outbreak] has made dozens of people
sick. Judges, lawyers, inmates in the jail, and several people in the
courthouse cafeteria have come down with the intestinal virus.

Health officials believe the virus was spread through the courthouse
cafeteria, Vancouver Coastal Health Authority spokeswoman Viviana
Zanocco said. "We'll know we have it under control when we go a
couple of days without anyone else getting sick," Zanocco said. "That
hasn't happened yet." Zanocco said an environmental health officer is
monitoring the cleanup daily. No one has been serious ill.

